      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, that makes sense. i noticed you mentioned specific colors and styles like navy or charcoal suits for men and modest, subdued styles for women as the way to look \"refined.\" \n\ni'm wondering though, if we are trying to make this a \"universal\" guide, shouldn't we also include examples of professional sophistication from other parts of the world? like, how would someone in Lagos, Tokyo, or Mumbai express that same level of \"high-level corporate\" sophistication? i want to make sure my readers don't feel like this guide only applies to western-style offices.",
