      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're absolutely right, it's important to highlight that there are different but equally sophisticated ways of displaying professionalism around the globe.\n\n1. **Lagos (Africa):**\n   - **Men:** In Lagos, minimalistic but neat suits in black, white, and dark grey are the go-to choices. Afros or shaved heads remain popular for men but combine them with tailored suits. Accessories can include simple, understated ties and smart watches.\n   - **Women:** Modest and professional dresses in nondescript colors, tailored trousers are also in fashion for women. Long sleeves and skirts are common for formal events, with minimalistic jewelry and heels that balance comfort and elegance.\n\n2. **Tokyo (Asia):**\n   - **Men:** Professional attire in Tokyo usually includes tailored suits in navy and grey. Japanese men prefer simplicity and a tie, with partial suits becoming more acceptable (partial suits are shorter or sometimes just the pants). Dark, professional shoes are a given.\n   - **Women:** For women, Tokyo favors both traditional and modern outfits. A well-dressed J-Style school uniform from a prestigious institution, or simple tailored dresses in neutral tones, are common. Long sleeves and modest fitting dresses for formal settings, paired with minimalistic jewelry.\n\n3",
